  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: human-errors gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Perfusionists configure pump speed and flow targets intraoperatively; however, all validation activities were conducted assuming correctly specified boundary conditions and nominal operator inputs. No use-error modes, misuse scenarios, or operator training gaps were characterized or evaluated.",
