      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria documented; solver iteration convergence demonstrated for all production runs.",
      "rationale": "All simulation runs converged to residual tolerance 1e-5 for continuity and momentum, 1e-6 for turbulence equations. Convergence plots archived. Required level 1 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Characterization of operator error modes that could affect model inputs or interpretation of outputs in the clinical deployment context.",
      "rationale": "A single use-error scenario (flow-rate unit mismatch, L/hr vs L/min) was identified and mitigated by a pre-processing unit-check script. No systematic enumeration of operator error modes was performed. Perfusionist-introduced input variations (e.g., incorrect speed setpoints, misread patient weight for indexed flow targets, training-gap-driven parameter entry) were not modeled, not included in any validation activity, and are not bounded by the existing evidence. The achieved level is reported as 1 (documentation of solver use only); the required level of 2 for MRL 2 with HIGH decision consequence is not met, but this gap was not flagged during the credibility assessment review."
    },
