      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed on fluid viscosity (±15%), hematocrit (±5%), and inlet velocity profile (uniform vs. developed). Maximum RH sensitivity of 9.3% observed for viscosity variation. All inputs sourced from traceable calibrated measurements. Required level 2 met. Note: input sensitivity analysis assumed correctly specified nominal values; no analysis of inputs degraded by operator error was included."
